						               													<description>The board game bulls-bears about the stockpile. In the game you have to buy and sell stocks. The one who buys more than 50% of the shares wins. This is a board game with website interface. Website of the game is needed for make game mechanics easier.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game all players have the same amount of money and shares. Player can buy or sell min 1 and max 9 shares on the turn. The share price changes depending on the players' decision. If more shares were sold than purchased, the price falls; if the opposite is true, the price rises.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After a few days of trading, the shareholders' meeting begins. Participants choose the amount of dividends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when one of the participants buys more than 50 shares or becomes bankrupt.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
